0travelers%3C%2Fa%3E%20like%20me%20often%20sit%20next%20to%20a%20stranger.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20seats%20near%20the%20doors%20between%20cars%20are%20my%20least%20favorite.%20The%20doors%20open%20and%20close%20throughout%20the%20night%20as%20passengers%20and%20crew%20members%20walk%20through%20them.%20The%20area%20around%20them%20can%20be%20noisy%2C%20and%20I%20typically%20get%20a%20rough%20night's%20sleep%20when%20I'm%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDefinitely%20use%20noise-canceling%20headphones%20or%20earplugs%20if%20you're%20sitting%20in%20that%20area.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EKeep%20your%20essential%20items%20in%20a%20bag%20that's%20easily%20accessible%20from%20your%20seat.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223456%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22coach%20area%20on%20southwest%20chief%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F63bc73e006706e0019a9845d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222599%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20view%20from%20my%20coach%20seat%20on%20the%20Southwest%20Chief.%3Cp%3EJill%20Dutton%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20you'll%20either%20check%20your%20luggage%20or%20leave%20it%20in%20a%20stowaway%20compartment%2C%20put%20your%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-bring-one-bag-on-trips-packing-tips-2022-8%5C%22%3Emost%20important%20items%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20a%20backpack%20you%20can%20keep%20at%20your%20seat.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELoad%20the%20backpack%20with%20anything%20you'll%20need%20while%20traveling.%20Pack%20medications%2C%20a%20few%20bottles%20of%20water%2C%20wet%20wipes%2C%20a%20change%20of%20clothes%2C%20a%20sleeping%20mask%2C%20ear%20plugs%2C%20a%20toothbrush%2C%20a%20tube%20of%20toothpaste%2C%20and%20a%20book%20or%20deck%20of%20cards%20%E2%80%94%20entertainment%20for%20when%20the%20train%20doesn't%20have%20WiFi%20available.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20usually%20plenty%20of%20legroom%20and%20space%20to%20store%20my%20backpack%20below%20the%20seat%20in%20front%20of%20me