r%20columnist%3F%20Write%20to%20For%20Love%20%26amp%3B%20Money%20using%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdocs.google.com%2Fforms%2Fd%2Fe%2F1FAIpQLSdhFnAxR57cNtGiwNUd-6vLAYAc75grvly3C10-854vFP4arw%2Fviewform%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethis%20Google%20form%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDear%20For%20Love%20%26amp%3B%20Money%2C%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20recently%20lost%20my%20job.%20I%20had%20long-standing%20differences%20with%20my%20boss%20that%20came%20to%20a%20boiling%20point%2C%20and%20I%20got%20fired.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMy%20husband%20is%20upset%20with%20me%20because%20he%20feels%20I%20should%20have%20had%20a%20higher%20tolerance%20for%20my%20ex-boss's%20toxic%20behavior%20in%20order%20to%20protect%20our%20family's%20financial%20security.%20I%20find%20this%20frustrating%20because%20my%20husband%20makes%20enough%20to%20pay%20our%20bills%2C%20and%20my%20income%20has%20always%20gone%20toward%20our%20quality%20of%20life.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EOur%20kids%20won't%20starve%20just%20because%20I'm%20between%20jobs%20right%20now.%20I%20am%20already%20searching%20for%20a%20new%20position%2C%20and%20I%20am%20sure%20I%20will%20find%20one%20soon%2C%20but%20in%20the%20meantime%2C%20I%20don't%20think%20it's%20fair%20that%20my%20husband%20resents%20me%20for%20getting%20out%20of%20a%20bad%20situation.%20How%20do%20I%20convince%20him%20I%20did%20the%20right%20thing%20by%20standing%20up%20for%20myself%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESincerely%2C%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EI'd%20Do%20It%20Again%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDear%20I'd%20Do%20It%20Again%2C%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20asked%20me%20how%20to%20%26quot%3Bconvince%26quot%3B%20your%20husband%20that%20you%20did%20the%20right%20thing%2C%20but%20I'm%20not%20sure%20that%20will%20be%20the%20most%20effective%20or%20honest%20strategy%20for%20helping%20your%20family%20through%20this%20challenging%20season.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFirst%2C%20I%20suggest%20you%20handle%20the%20practical%20side%20of%20your%20job%20loss.%20Tie%20up%20any%20loose%20ends%20with%20your%20previous%20employers%20so%20that%20you%20can%20collect%20your%20final%20check%20and%20receive%20any%20severance%20you%20have%20coming%20your%20way.%20File%20for%20unemployment%2C%20and%20go%20over%20your%20family's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbanking%2Fbest-budgeting-apps%5C%22%3Ebudget%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20making%20adjustments%20that%20reflect%20your%20loss%20of%20income.%20Have%20a%20plan%20for%20whether%20you'll%20move%20your%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fwhat-is-401k%5C%22%3E401(k)%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20your%20new%20employer's%20plan%20or%20if%20you%20instead%20want%20to%20put%20the%20money%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fbest-rollover-ira%5C%22%3Erollover%20IRA%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELook%20into%20your%20family's%20health%20insurance%20options.%20Maybe%20you%20all%20are%20covered%20by%20your%20husband's%20employer%20already%2C%20but%20if%20not%2C%20check%20into%20what%20options%20make%20the%20most%20sense%20for%20your%20family%20now.%20You%20might%20look%20into%20COBRA%20until%20you%20get%20a%20new%20job%20or%20move%20your%20family%20onto%20your%20husband's%20insurance.%20You%20can%20see%20if%20you%20qualify%20for%20special%20enrollment%20in%20the%20marketplace%2C%20or%20you%20might%20even%20look%20into%20a%20combination%20of%20direct%20primary%20care%20membership%20and%20critical%20illness%20insurance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20administrative%20tasks%20are%20imperative%20to%20your%20family's%20security%2C%20but%20tackling%20them%20with%20energy%20and%20alacrity%20will%20have%20the%20added%20benefit%20of%20showing%20your%20husband%20that%20you%20are%20aware%20of%20your%20responsibility%20and%20care%20deeply%20about%20it.%20You%20will%20also%20model%20for%20your%20husband%20what%20he%20seems%20to%20be%20missing%2C%20which%20is%20%E2%80%94%20what's%20done%20is%20done.%20There's%20nothing%20to%20be%20gained%20from%20anger%20and%20recriminations.%20It's%20time%20to%20solve%20the%20crisis%2C%20not%20yell%20about%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20make%20no%20mistake%20%E2%80%94%20at%20least%20to%20your%20husband%2C%20it%20is%20a%20crisis.%20If%20it's%20a%20crisis%20for%20him%2C%20it's%20a%20crisis%20for%20you%20both.%20Losing%20a%20stream%20of%20income%20is%20always%20terrifying.%20While%20your%20husband%20may%20cover%20your%20bills%2C%20you%20said%20yourself%20that%20your%20check%20has%20always%20covered%20your%20quality%20of%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20sudden%20lifestyle%20descent%20is%20jarring%2C%20and%20the%20changes%20you%20must%20make%20will%20likely%20make%20everyone%20in%20your%20family%20feel%20insecure%20at%20first.%20The%20small%20practices%20we%20use%20to%20hold%20our%20families%20together%2C%20such%20as%20youth%20sports%2C%20family%20vacations%2C%20and%20pizza%20nights%2C%20are%20typically%20the%20first%20to%20go%20when%20things%20are%20tight.%20Ripping%20these%20away%20can%20make%20it%20seem%20like%20everything%20is%20falling%20apart.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYour%20husband%20will%20feel%20this%20the%20most.%20The%20financial%20weight%20of%20a%20family%20is%20heavy.%20Up%20until%20recently%2C%20that%20weight%20was%20carried%20by%20two%20working%20adults.%20But%20with%20you%20out%20of%20the%20workforce%2C%20your%20family's%20livelihood%20depends%20on%20him.%20A%20layer%20of%20security%20has%20been%20removed%2C%20and%20now%20he%20probably%20worries%20that%20he's%20one%20job%20loss%20away%20from%20losing%20everything.%20As%20maddening%20as%20it%20may%20feel%20to%20see%20your%20husband%20react%20so%20poorly%20to%20something%20that%20primarily%20happened%20to%20you%2C%20remember%20that%20this%20affected%20him%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20isn't%20to%20say%20you%20did%20the%20wrong%20thing%20by%20standing%20up%20for%20yourself%20at%20the%20cost%20of%20your%20job.%20I%20hope%20you%20honor%20your%20emotional%20process%20here%20as%20well%20as%20your%20husband's.%20Even%20when%20you%20hate%20your%20boss%2C%20there's%20a%20grief%20that%20accompanies%20the%20rejection%20of%20getting%20fired.%20It's%20so%20easy%20to%20go%20over%20and%20over%20what%20you%20could%20have%20done%2C%20how%20it%20should%20have%20gone%2C%20and%20all%20the%20people%20who%20misunderstood%20and%20betrayed%20you%20along%20the%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPainting%20over%20vulnerable%20emotions%20like%20hurt%20and%20grief%20with%20a%20thick%20coat%20of%20anger%20can%20often%20feel%20easier%20than%20sitting%20with%20the%20ache%20of%20it.%20Investigate%20what%20might%20be%20going%20on%20underneath%20your%20defense%20mechanisms.%20You%20may%20find%20they%20are%20the%20real%20reason%20you%20want%20to%20%26quot%3Bconvince%26quot%3B%20your%20husband%20that%20you%20did%20the%20right%20thing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EImagine%20achieving%20that%20goal.%20In%20this%20version%20of%20events%2C%20your%20husband%20wouldn't%20make%20you%20feel%20ashamed%20for%20taking%20care%20of%20yourself.%20Your%20husband%20would%20support%20and%20believe%20you%20when%20you%20told%20him%20how%20unbearable%20your%20work%20situation%20had%20become.%20Your%20husband%20would%20be%20less%20concerned%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbanking%2Fbest-banks%5C%22%3Ebank%20accounts%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20more%20about%20helping%20you%20through%20this.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20convincing%20him%20shouldn't%20be%20your%20goal%2C%20there%20must%20be%20a%20reckoning%20over%20both%20of%20your%20emotional%20experiences.%20I%20know%20that%20he%20has%20been%20unpleasantly%20honest%20about%20how%20angry%20he%20feels%20that%20you%20couldn't%20just%20suck%20it%20up%20and%20play%20ball%20to%20stay%20gainfully%20employed%2C%20but%20just%20behind%20that%20anger%20likely%20sits%20his