80%94%20but%20not%20particularly%20high%20value%20%E2%80%94%20can%20be%20automated%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Gerratana%2C%20who%20advises%20clients%20on%20intellectual%20property%20issues.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20the%20integration%20of%20AI%20into%20law%20firms%2C%20Gerratana%20said%20he%20can%20picture%20a%20world%20where%20hour-based%20billing%2C%20subscription-type%20billing%2C%20and%20task-based%20billing%20for%20legal%20services%20all%20exist%20at%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20I%2C%20as%20an%20attorney%2C%20can%20really%20speed%20up%20my%20work%20I%20might%20be%20more%20inclined%26quot%3B%20to%20bill%20by%20the%20task%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22bf826b9d-4af6-4b2e-b1a7-362abf3e58f6%5C%22%3EA%202023%20ABA%20survey%20found%20that%2020%25%20of%20law%20firms%20were%20using%20or%20considering%20using%20AI%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20a%202023%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.americanbar.org%2Fgroups%2Flaw_practice%2Fresources%2Ftech-report%2F2023%2F2023-artificial-intelligence-ai-techreport%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esurvey%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fstudent-loans%2Fis-law-school-worth-it%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmerican%20Bar%20Association%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20that%2010.9%25%20of%20firms%20across%20all%20sizes%20were%20using%20AI%20tools%20in%20their%20practices%2C%20while%209.8%25%20were%20seriously%20considering%20purchasing%20AI%20tools.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGatto%20said%20that%20his%20firm%20utilizes%20a%20custom%20AI%20tool%20that%20was%20developed%20in-house.%20The%20tool%20can%20be%20used%20to%20draft%20legal%20memos%20and%20briefs%20and%20to%20create%20initial%20agreements%20of%20all%20kinds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBasically%20any%20type%20of%20legal%20document%2C%20you%20can%20use%20AI%20to%20some%20extent%2C%20at%20least%20right%20now%2C%20to%20assist%20in%20creating%20a%20first%20draft%2C%26quot%3B%20Gatto%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20use%20of%20AI%2C%20Sheppard%20Mullin%20is%20still%20currently%20charging%20clients%20by%20the%20hour.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20part%20that's%20being%20done%20by%20AI%2C%20we're%20charging%20still%20just%20hourly.%20If%20it%20takes%20five%20minutes%2C%20we%20bill%20five%20minutes%2C%20that's%20it%2C%20but%20none%20of%20that%20stuff%20is%20ready%20to%20go%20to%20the%20client%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Gatto%2C%20explaining%20that%20an%20initial%20draft%20of%20a%20document%20created%20with%20the%20help%20of%20AI%20would%20be%20comparable%20to%20the%20work%20of%20a%20first-year%20law%20school%20student.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20still%20a%20fair%20amount%20of%20work%20that%20gets%20done%20between%20the%20partner%20and%20the%20first%20year%20to%20get%20the%20memo%20to%20the%20point%20where%20it%20takes%20everything%20into%20account%20and%20it's%20ready%20to%20go%20to%20a%20client%2C%26quot%3B%20Gatto%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20firms%20Curtis%20and%20Mintz%20are%20still%20in%20the%20piloting%20phase%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20the%20use%20of%20AI%20in%20legal%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAny%20law%20firm%20that%20is%20not%20currently%20investigating%20how%20to%20use%20AI%20tools%20in%20their%20practice%20is%20going%20to%20fall%20quickly%20behind%20the%20law%20firms%20that%20have%20figured%20this%20out%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Gerratana.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJuan%20Perla%2C%20another%20partner%20at%20Curtis%2C%20said%20that%20the%20firm%20is%20in%20the%20midst%20of%20developing%20an%20internal%20AI%20policy%20and%20expects%20to%20have%20certain%20AI%20tools%20integrated%20into%20the%20practice%20within%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAlthough%20we're%20proceeding%20carefully%20we're%20very%20intentional%20in%20our%20plan%20moving%20forward%2C%26quot%3B%20Botero%20added.%20%26quot%3BWe%20do%20feel%20that%20these%20tools%20will%20be%20necessary.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERichard%20Robinson%2C%20the%20CEO%20and%20founder%20of%20the%20legal%20tech%20startup%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpitch-deck-legal-tech-startup-robin-ai-raise-series-b-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERobin%20AI%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20which%20uses%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fanthropic-claude-chatbot-google-chatgpt-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAnthropic's%3C%2Fa%3E%20large%20language%20model%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fresearchers-at-anthropic-taught-these-ai-chatbots-how-to-lie-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EClaude%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20help%20lawyers%20draft%20and%20edit%20contracts%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20tools%20like%20his%20enable%20attorneys%20to%20operate%20at%20the%20top%20of%20their%20game.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20not%20just%20revolutionizing%20the%20legal%20industry.%20We're%20helping%20businesses%20to%20grow%2C%26quot%3B%20Robinson%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe've%20helped%20companies%20do%20legal%20due%20diligence%2010%20times%20faster%20than%20they%20could%20without%20our%20technology.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20are%20helping%20companies%20to%20reduce%20the%20time%20it%20takes%20to%20negotiate%20contracts%20from%2090%20days%20down%20to%20seven%2C%20in%20some%20cases%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Robinson%2C%20Robin%20AI%2C%20which%20was%20founded%20in%202019%2C%20has%20100%20paying%20customers%2C%20including%20seven%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftop-fortune-500-companies-addressing-diversity-and-inclusion-2021-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFortune%20500%20%3C%2Fa%3Ecompanies%2C%20as%20well%20as%20thousands%20of%20users%20utilizing%20a%20free%20version%20of%20the%20product.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20are%20seeing%20enormous%20demand%20ever%20since%20the%20release%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feverything-you-need-to-know-about-chat-gpt-2023-1%5C%22%20targ